 the crypto asset. =E2=80=A6
Additionally, in or around September 2019, Coinbase and other crypto asset =
businesses founded the Crypto Rating Council (=E2=80=9CCRC=E2=80=9D). The C=
RC subsequently released a framework for analyzing crypto assets that =E2=
=80=9Cdistilled a set of yes or no questions which are designed to plainly =
address each of the four Howey test factors=E2=80=9D and assigned to the cr=
ypto asset a score ranging from 1 to 5, with a score of 1 indicating that a=
n =E2=80=9Casset has few or no characteristics consistent with treatment as=
 an investment contract,=E2=80=9D and a score of 5 meaning that an =E2=80=
=9Casset has many characteristics strongly consistent with treatment as a s=
ecurity.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
In announcing the CRC=E2=80=99s creation, Coinbase stated, =E2=80=9C[a]ltho=
ugh the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission has issued helpful guidance=
, whether any given crypto asset is a security ultimately requires a fact-i=
ntensive analysis.=E2=80=9D

Very responsible, though the SEC disagrees with Coinbase=E2=80=99s conclusi=
ons and has quibbles with the process:
Between late 2019 and the end of 2020, Coinbase more than doubled the numbe=
r of crypto assets available for trading on the Coinbase Platform, and it m=
ore than doubled that number again in 2021. During this period, Coinbase ma=
de available on the Coinbase Platform crypto assets with high =E2=80=9Crisk=
=E2=80=9D scores under the CRC framework it had adopted. In other words, to=
