<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">With Binance, the answer is more interesting. =
Binance is, as crypto exchanges go, sort of an average amount of law-abidin=
g? It is notoriously opaque, headquartered nowhere, a web of confusing enti=
ties designed to avoid regulation. (The SEC quotes its chief compliance off=
icer saying, in 2018, =E2=80=9Cwe do not want [Binance].com to be regulated=
 ever.=E2=80=9D) Like FTX, it has its own token, called BNB; it has its own=
 affiliated trading firms; it has separate platforms for US customers (Bina=
nce.us) and for the rest of the world (Binance.com). It was <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31711038.259416/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
